50 agents reviewed 8 categories 2026 pricing verified Zero sponsored placements

The customer support AI market hit a structural shift in 2026. Parloa's industry research: 85% of customer service leaders explored or piloted GenAI, and by 2026, 40% of enterprise applications integrate task-specific AI agents (up from less than 5% in 2025). The conversational AI market is projected to reach $41B by 2030, growing 23.7% annually. The question is no longer whether to deploy AI for support; it is which agent fits your stack.

And there are now far too many to evaluate by reading. Activant Capital documents Sierra, Cresta, and Replicant each raising $100M+, Uniphore at $600M+, and a long tail of well-funded specialists. Twenty-plus serious players compete for the same enterprise contact center budget. Without a category map, every buying conversation drifts toward whichever vendor's salesperson is loudest.

This guide is the map. 50 agents organized into 8 categories you should evaluate separately. The first section explains why this listicle is structured by category instead of ranked 1-50: ranking apples against oranges produces the wrong answer for everyone. Pairs with our 50 Best AI Sales Agents, 50 Best AI Marketing Agents, and Agentic AI Explained.

