#01

Sierra

Enterprise CX agents with cross-session memory

STRENGTHSConstellation of 15+ AI models from OpenAI/Anthropic/Meta auto-selecting per task. Cross-session memory makes agents remember prior interactions. Reached $100M ARR faster than almost any enterprise AI company. Outcome-based pricing.

BEST FITConsumer brands with millions of customers and complex support operations where continuity matters.

#02

Decagon

Agent Operating Procedures (AOPs) for enterprise governance

STRENGTHSFounded 2023 by Jesse Zhang and Ashwin Sreenivas. Raised $231M total including $131M Series C from Andreessen Horowitz and Accel. Customers include Notion, Duolingo, Substack, Bilt, Rippling, ClassPass. 74% auto-resolution rates documented in fintech deployments.

BEST FITHigh-volume support operations needing structured agent behavior, multilingual support, and compliance controls.

#03

Ada

No-code automation across 50+ languages

STRENGTHSMulti-LLM orchestration for brand-safe responses. APIs and SDKs for enterprise integration. No-code Playbooks let CX teams build workflows without engineering. Documented integrations for Shopify, Salesforce, Zendesk. ACX model provides structured services alongside the platform.

BEST FITMid-market and enterprise brands wanting control over agent behavior without code, with strong multilingual needs.

#04

Forethought

Multi-agent system for ticket triage, routing, summarization

STRENGTHSSpecialized agents for different tasks: Solve (deflection), Triage (routing), Assist (agent help), Discover (knowledge gap detection). Plugs into existing helpdesks rather than replacing them. Discover Agent identifies knowledge gaps that reduce deflection quality.

BEST FITTeams with deep ticket histories who want AI augmentation across an existing Zendesk/Salesforce/Freshdesk stack rather than wholesale replacement.

#05

Maven AGI

Generative customer experience platform

STRENGTHSStandalone AI agent that overlays on existing ticketing system via API. Designed for autonomous resolution of complex multi-step requests. Strong on cross-channel orchestration including chat, email, voice, SMS, and social.

BEST FITEnterprises wanting to keep their existing helpdesk but add a sophisticated AI agent layer on top with autonomous action capability.

#06

Salesforce Agentforce

Agentic layer for the Salesforce ecosystem

STRENGTHSNative to Service Cloud and the broader Salesforce platform. Inherits Salesforce's data model, permissions, and governance. Strong integration with Sales Cloud for cross-functional workflows. Extends to Slack, MuleSoft, Tableau.

BEST FITSalesforce-centric organizations wanting AI agents that share data with sales, marketing, and service in one platform.

#07

Cognigy

Hybrid rule-based + AI for regulated industries

STRENGTHSStrong vertical focus on manufacturing and financial services. On-premise deployment options for compliance-heavy organizations. Robust workflow engine with formal governance. German engineering with European data residency.

BEST FITRegulated enterprises (banking, insurance, healthcare) with on-premise requirements and hybrid rule + AI workflow needs.

#08

Kore.ai

Conversational AI platform spanning support, employee, and process automation

STRENGTHSGartner-recognized leader. XO Platform for low-code conversation flow design. Spans external customer support, internal employee assistance, and broader business process automation in one platform.

BEST FITOrganizations wanting one platform for both customer-facing and internal AI agents, with support, employee help desk, and process automation needs.

